Pages = {517-520},
Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {Additional information on hawkmoth visits to flowers of 24 species in
   the continental United States is presented to enlarge the data base. We
   now have hawkmoth pollination records for 41 native species and
   visitation records for at least three naturalized species in the
   temperate North American flora. The total number of native
   sphingophilous species in this flora is 106. The most important
   sphingophilous plant group of supraspecific taxonomic rank in temperate
   North America is the tribe  Onagreae (family Onagraceae). The evolution
   of the hawkmoth pollination system in this group is discussed.},
